  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is the fluid mosaic model, and who proposed it?": "流体马赛克模型是什么? 谁提出它?",
  "The fluid mosaic model (Singer & Nicolson, 1972): (1) 'Fluid' = phospholipids and most proteins are not fixed in place — they move laterally within the plane of the membrane (lateral diffusion). Demonstrated by Frye & Edidin (1970) cell fusion experiment: fluorescently labeled human and mouse membrane proteins intermixed within 40 minutes. (2) 'Mosaic' = the membrane contains a diverse array of proteins (integral/transmembrane proteins that span the bilayer, peripheral proteins attached to surfaces) and other components (cholesterol, glycolipids, glycoproteins) creating a mosaic pattern. (3) Replaced earlier models: Davson-Danielli 'sandwich' model (1935) — proposed protein coated both surfaces of a lipid bilayer. Robertson's unit membrane model (1960s) — proposed all biological membranes were identical. (4) Key features: asymmetry (inner and outer leaflets differ in lipid and protein composition), fluidity (varies with temperature, fatty acid saturation, cholesterol content), and selectivity (controls what enters/exits the cell).": "流体马赛克模型(Singer & Nicolson,1972年):(1) 流体马赛克模型(Singer & Nicolson,1972年):(1) “Fluid” =磷素和大多数蛋白质没有固定到位——它们平流地在膜的平面内移动(侧面扩散);Frye & Edidin(1970年)演示的细胞聚变实验:在40分钟内交错使用荧光标记的人类蛋白和鼠标膜蛋白;(2) “Mosaic” =membrane 包含多种蛋白质(双层、表面附着的边缘蛋白蛋白质)和其他成分(胆固醇、甘蓝、甘蓝蛋白质),形成一种马赛克模式。 (3) 取代以前的模型:Davson-Danielli'sandwich'模型(1935年)——提议的蛋白质涂层两层的蛋白质表面。罗伯逊的单位膜模型(1960年s)——拟议的所有生物膜蛋白质模型都相同。 (4) 关键特征:恒定性(内含性成分、异性化学成分、异性),以及化学温度温度的成分)。",
  "What is the structure of a phospholipid, and why does its amphipathic nature drive membrane formation?": "磷蛋白质的结构是什么,为什么其两栖病原性质会驱动膜形成?",
  "Phospholipid structure and membrane formation: (1) Structure: glycerol backbone with two fatty acid tails (hydrophobic, typically 16-18 carbons, one often unsaturated with a cis double bond creating a kink) and one phosphate head group (hydrophilic, often modified with choline, ethanolamine, serine, or inositol → phosphatidylcholine, phosphatidylethanolamine, phosphatidylserine, phosphatidylinositol). (2) Amphipathic = having both hydrophilic and hydrophobic regions. (3) Self-assembly: in aqueous solution, phospholipids spontaneously form bilayers to minimize hydrophobic exposure to water — thermodynamically favorable (increases entropy of surrounding water). Can also form micelles (single layer, tails inward) or liposomes (bilayer spheres). (4) Bilayer properties: ~5 nm thick. Hydrophobic core prevents passage of ions and polar molecules. Flexible — can bend, fuse, and bud. Self-sealing — if punctured, phospholipids rearrange to close the gap.": "磷磷脂结构和膜形成:(1) 结构: 甘蓝脊柱,有两种脂肪酸尾巴(疏水性,一般为16-18碳,其中一种往往不饱和,带有产生动脉的双环结合)和一种磷酸盐头组(嗜水性,经常用胆碱、乙醇胺、醋酸盐、醋酸盐或异硫醇-磷酸丁酯、磷酸甲酯乙基乙醇胺、磷酸丁丁酯、磷酸丁醇醇));(2) 氨虫性脊柱,有两种脂肪酸酸尾巴,有两种脂肪酸盐酸盐酸盐酸盐(典型为16-18碳,其中一种通常不饱和,其中一种为产生催泪性双层,以尽量减少对水的防水接触——热动力上有利的(增加周围水的酶),也可以形成老鼠(单层、尾向内)或脂质(双层)。 (4) 双层特性:~5纳米厚; 氢恐惧核心防止离子和极分子的通过。 (3) 自组合:可以弯、导、导体和深层-如果隔裂-接近-离层,可弯、导-接近-接近- 底。",
  "Outliers and Resistant Measures": "外围和抵抗措施",
  "HIV entry and membrane proteins: (1) HIV entry steps: gp120 (viral surface glycoprotein) binds CD4 receptor (integral membrane protein on T-helper cells, macrophages, dendritic cells) → conformational change in gp120 exposes co-receptor binding site → gp120 binds CCR5 or CXCR4 (chemokine receptors, 7-transmembrane GPCRs) → conformational change in gp41 (viral transmembrane protein) → fusion peptide of gp41 inserts into host membrane → viral and host membranes fuse → viral capsid enters cell. (2) CCR5-Δ32 mutation: 32 base pair deletion in CCR5 gene → premature stop codon → truncated protein not expressed on cell surface. Homozygotes (Δ32/Δ32, ~1% of European descent): highly resistant to R5-tropic HIV strains. Heterozygotes: slower disease progression. (3) Clinical application: maraviroc (CCR5 antagonist drug) blocks the co-receptor. Timothy Brown ('Berlin patient') — received bone marrow transplant from CCR5-Δ32 homozygous donor → functionally cured of HIV. (4) Demonstrates: how specific integral membrane proteins serve as viral receptors, and how membrane protein mutations can confer disease resistance.": "艾滋病毒入口和薄膜蛋白:(1) 艾滋病毒进入步骤: gp120 (湿表面甘蓝蛋白) 将 CD4 受体(T- helper 细胞、大型phage 和 dendritic 细胞上的综合膜蛋白质蛋白质质)粘合) Gp120 的相容变化暴露了共同受体结合点  gp120 结合了CCCR5 或 CXCR4 (化学受体受体, 7Tymembrane GGCR) 和 gp41 (阳表面蛋白蛋白质蛋白质)的对应变化 ++ gp41 的混合蛋白质(在T- helmane 细胞细胞细胞细胞中插入了内膜的混合蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质 ) (2) CCR5-  32 突变异:32 过早停止使用细胞表面没有表现的 蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质蛋白质(crevle) (creal-ral demologyrusal rationrus rationrationration:",
  "A pharmaceutical company is developing a new drug delivery system using liposomes — artificial phospholipid bilayer vesicles that can encapsulate medications. How does the amphipathic nature of phospholipids make this technology possible, and what advantages do liposomes offer?": "一个制药公司正在利用脂质——人造磷素双层树脂囊,利用能够封装药物的脂质——开发一种新的药物运载系统。 磷素的两栖病原性质如何使这一技术成为可能? 脂质能提供什么好处?",
  "Liposome drug delivery — applied membrane biology: (1) Self-assembly: amphipathic phospholipids spontaneously form bilayer vesicles (liposomes, 50 nm-5 μm diameter) when dispersed in aqueous solution. Thermodynamically driven to minimize hydrophobic exposure to water. (2) Drug loading: hydrophilic drugs (e.g., doxorubicin for cancer — Doxil®) in aqueous interior; hydrophobic drugs (e.g., amphotericin B for fungal infections — AmBisome®) within lipid bilayer; amphipathic drugs at the bilayer-water interface. (3) Advantages: biocompatible and biodegradable; reduce systemic toxicity (cancer drugs reach tumor preferentially via EPR effect — enhanced permeability and retention); protect drugs from degradation; can be modified with PEG (stealth liposomes — avoid immune clearance) or targeting ligands (antibodies, peptides) for cell-specific delivery. (4) mRNA vaccines (Pfizer/Moderna COVID-19): use lipid nanoparticles (related to liposomes) to deliver mRNA into cells — the lipid bilayer protects fragile mRNA and facilitates cellular uptake via endocytosis.": "• 药物负荷:水性内水性药物(例如,用于癌症的多克菌素-多克西里氏菌);"
